File: Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth. Pic: Marco Longari / AFP JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 related deaths in South Africa have passed the 18,000 mark. The Department of Health reported 165 more COVID-19 related deaths on Tuesday. The death toll in the country now stands at 18,028. Over 1,100 new cases have been identified since the last report. That brings the total number of COVID-19 infections in South Africa to 694, 537, but with a recovery rate of 90-percent, there are just over 50,000 active cases in the country. Health Media Statement 13 October 2020.Pages Final (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd 